{
  "doc_id": "39254",
  "text": "UGT2B7 is capable of conjugating a wide variety of xenobiotics and endogenous steroids. Substrates include androsterone, morphine, codeine, lorazepam, propranolol, and nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs [CITATION_1] . UGT2B7 is an inducible enzyme (Munzel et al., 1999) and has more than 10 single nucleotide polymorphisms [CITATION_2] . Identification of the UGT2B7 isozyme responsible for gemfibrozil glucuronidation will prove to be an invaluable tool in identifying the impact of UGT2B7 polymorphisms on the variability associated with gemfibrozil pharmacokinetics and magnitude of drug-drug interactions. ",
  "correct_citation": {
